| **Field**                  | **Description / Example**                                                                                                                          |
| -------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Test Case ID**           | TC-LOGIN-001                                                                                                                                       |
| **Requirement/User Story** | US-123 – As a user, I should be able to login with valid credentials.                                                                              |
| **Test Case Title**        | Verify successful login with valid credentials                                                                                                     |
| **Pre-Conditions**         | - User is registered in the system<br>- Application is accessible<br>- Correct test data available                                                 |
| **Test Data**              | Username = `test.user@example.com`<br>Password = `ValidPass123`                                                                                    |
| **Test Steps**             | 1. Launch the application URL<br>2. Enter username in the “Email” field<br>3. Enter password in the “Password” field<br>4. Click on “Login” button |
| **Expected Result**        | - User is redirected to dashboard page<br>- Welcome message is displayed with username<br>- Session cookie is created successfully                 |
| **Post-Conditions**        | User is logged into the application                                                                                                                |
| **Priority**               | High                                                                                                                                               |
| **Type**                   | Functional – Positive                                                                                                                              |
| **Automation Feasibility** | Yes (Playwright/Selenium)                                                                                                                          |
| **Execution Status**       | Pass / Fail (to be updated during execution)                                                                                                       |
| **Comments/Notes**         | Can be reused as precondition for regression cases involving “logged-in user” scenarios                                                            |

Negative test case 

| **Field**                  | **Description / Example**                                                                                                            |
| -------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| **Test Case ID**           | TC-LOGIN-002                                                                                                                         |
| **Requirement/User Story** | US-123 – As a user, I should not be allowed to login with invalid credentials.                                                       |
| **Test Case Title**        | Verify login fails with incorrect password                                                                                           |
| **Pre-Conditions**         | User is registered in the system                                                                                                     |
| **Test Data**              | Username = `test.user@example.com`<br>Password = `WrongPass!`                                                                        |
| **Test Steps**             | 1. Launch the application URL<br>2. Enter username in the “Email” field<br>3. Enter incorrect password<br>4. Click on “Login” button |
| **Expected Result**        | - Login attempt is rejected<br>- Error message displayed: *“Invalid username or password”*<br>- User is not redirected to dashboard  |
| **Priority**               | High                                                                                                                                 |
| **Type**                   | Functional – Negative                                                                                                                |
| **Automation Feasibility** | Yes                                                                                                                                  |
| **Execution Status**       | To be updated  |


Clarity (steps written clearly)
Traceability (linked to requirement ID)
Positive & Negative coverage
Reusability (common login steps as preconditions)
Repeatability (defined test data)
Maintainability (separate test data section for updates)
